{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The study of attentional guidance focuses on the factors that modulate activations on the overall priority map.",
    "Several sources of attentional guidance have been distinguished, among which are visual salience, observers' goals, selection history, and scene guidance.",
    "These sources are thought to jointly influence activations on the priority map.",
    "Therefore, the peak on this map depends on the relative strengths of the different guiding factors at any given moment.",
    "Note that while this peak is often thought to determine where attention will be shifted next, other suggestions have been put forward (see, e.g., Moran et al., 2013, for a probabilistic relation between priority and attention allocations; Yaron & Lamy, 2021, for the idea that contextual information constrains when the next shift of attention to the peak on the priority map is triggered)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
